owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a parameterized type to each of its actual type arguments
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: actual type argument

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a code element to its annotations
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: annotation

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a executable invocation to each of its actual arguments
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: argument

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links an arrray to the type of its elements at the finest grain. For instance, an array of type "int[][][]" is linked to the type "int".
Links an assert statement to the boolean expression asserted to be true
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: assert expression

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links an executable or a statement to its body
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: body

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a try statement to the relative catch clauses
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: catch

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a catch clause to its formal parameters, namely the throwable it caughts
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: catch formal parameter

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies a condition for a statement to be executed
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: condition

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links an executable to the classes it constructs
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: constructs

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a variable to the statement it was declared by
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: declaration

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a code element to the element it is declared by
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: declared by

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a project to its dependencies
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: dependency

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a if-then-else statement to the statement in the else branch
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: else

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a statement to the expressions it contains
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: expression

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a class, an interface, a type variable or a wildacard to the types it extends
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: extends

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a try statemet to its finally clause
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: finally

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a basic for statement to each statement expression executed as initialization code, before the first iteration step is performed
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: for init

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a basic for statement to each expression evaluated as update code at the end of every iteration
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: for update

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a class, an interface, an enumeration, a constructor or a method to the formal type parameters it declares
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: formal type parameter

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a parameterized type to the generic type it is a parameterization of
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: generic type

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a class to each implemented interface
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: implements

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a variable declaration to the expression assigned to the declared variable
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: initializer

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a invocation expression to the invoked executable
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: invokes

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a assignement expression to the left hand side expression
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: left hand side

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a modifiable elemet to its modifiers
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: modifier

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a statement to the next statement to be executed
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: next

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a method to the method it overrides
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: overrides

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a constructor or a method to the formal parameters it declares
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: parameter

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a method or a constructor to the types, methods, constructors and fields it requests.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: requests

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a try statement to each local variable declared to act as resource for the try statement
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: resource

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a return statement to the returned expression
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: returned expression

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a method to its return type
Links a method to the variable it returns, if any
Links a block of code to the statements it contains
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: statement

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a project to its subprojects
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: subproject

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a lower bounded wildcard to its bouds
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: super

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a switch statement to its switch label
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: switch label

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a method invocation expression to its target
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: target

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a if-then-else statement to the statement declared in the "then" branch
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: then

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a thrown statement to the expression it throws
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: thrown expression

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a method or a constructor to the exceptions it declares to throw
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: throws

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links an expression, a variable or a method to its type
Links a for-each statement to the local variable it declares

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a statement to the line it starts in
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: line

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The actual argument of a method
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Actual Argument

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An assignment expression. It involves one of the following operators: =, *=, /=, %=, +=, -=, <<=, >>=, >>>=, &=, ^=, |=
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Assignment Expression

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A branching statement is either a break statement, a continue statement or a return statement
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Branching Statement

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class defines a break statement. The break statement has two forms: labeled and unlabeled. In case a break statement is labeled, the label is defined through the targetedLabel property
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Break Statement

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class defines a catch clause
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Catch clause

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A statement that corresponds to the declaration of a local class
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Class Declaration Statement

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An expression that creates a class instance, in other words a constructor call
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Class Instance Creation Expression

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class defines a generic element in source code
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Code Element

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class defines a constructor of a Class
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Constructor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Control flow statements regulate the order in which statements get executed. They break up the flow of execution by employing decision making, looping, or branching.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Control Flow Statement

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Decision Making Statement is a statement that break up the flow of execution by employing decision making. It must either be a if-then-else statement or a switch statement
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Decision Making Statement

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A statement that holds a declaration
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Declaration statement

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class defines an executable block of code, namely a Method or a Constructor
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Executable

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This expression defines the invocation of either a method or a constructor.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Executable invocation expression

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A statement some expressions can be made into by terminating the expression with a semicolon.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Expression statement

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class defines a finally clause
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Finally clause

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A for-each statement, also known as enhanced for statement
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ForEach Statement

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class defines a switch label
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Label

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This expression defines a method call
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Method Invocation Expression

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A parameterized type is a particular parameterization of a generic type denoted by a specified list of type arguments
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Parameterized Type

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A synchronized statement, that is a statement that acquires a mutual-exclusion lock on behalf of the executiing-thread, executes a block, then release the lock. In java it is of the form: synchronized <Expression> <Block>
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Synchronized Statement

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A throw statement, that is a statement that causes an exception to be thrown
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Throw Statement

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class defines the actual type argument of a parameterized type
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Type Argument

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type variable is an unqualified identifier used as a type. It is introduced by the declaration of a generic class, interface, method, or constructor
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Type Variable

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A statement that represents the declaration of a variable
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Variable Declaration
